## The TPRM Register — Formalizing the Program

The TPRM program is documented in a vendor register that tracks each significant external dependency:

| Vendor | Category | Risk Level | Assurance Documents | Last Review | Next Review | HIPAA BAA | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| AWS | Infrastructure | High | SOC 2 Type II, ISO 27001, FedRAMP-authorized | [date] | [date + 1 year] | Executed [date] | Annual Artifact review |
| OpenMRS Community | Software Supply Chain | High | Community security advisories, GitHub security alerts | Ongoing (weekly M-1) | Ongoing | N/A — open source | Monthly Dependency-Check |
| LIS Provider [name] | Interconnected System | Moderate | ISA executed [date], BAA executed [date] | [date] | [date + 1 year] | Executed [date] | Annual contact verification |
| AWS WAF (managed rules) | Security Service | Moderate | Covered under AWS SOC 2 | With AWS review | With AWS review | Covered under AWS BAA | Included in AWS review |
| TOTP Authenticator App | Authentication Dependency | Low | App store security review | [date] | [date + 1 year] | N/A | Not in ePHI data path |

The TPRM register is reviewed as part of the annual continuous monitoring summary — not just the individual vendor reviews, but the register as a whole. Have any new dependencies been added during the year that should be in the register? Has any vendor's risk level changed based on the year's monitoring?

